12:59.712 --> 13:06.419 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
What they do have is looking at the variance
between where a number of the pre-election

13:06.519 --> 13:11.591 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
polls were in, of course, as we all know,
those were notoriously bad in these cases

13:11.691 --> 13:18.331 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
and where the vote count has come out, and
then some of the usual variances that you

13:18.431 --> 13:23.970 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
