20:08.174 --> 20:16.682 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
YANG: Nadja Drost in Bogota. Thanks for joining
us.

20:16.782 --> 20:22.321 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DROST: Thank you, john.

20:22.421 --> 20:29.361 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
YANG: Stay with us, coming up on the Newshour,
10 restaurants that changed America. Black

20:29.462 --> 20:35.201 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
south Africans entering a business that was
once off limits. And how a New York city deli

20:35.301 --> 20:43.375 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
brings people together. But first, the tragic
toll of substance abuses in America. A new

20:43.476 --> 20:48.881 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
surgeon general s report says it s not just
the heroin and opioid epidemic that s plaguing

20:48.981 --> 20:51.283 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
the country. William Brangham has more:

20:51.383 --> 20:54.820 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM, PBS CORRESPONDENT: According
to the surgeon general s report more than

20:54.920 --> 21:00.960 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
27 million Americans have problems with prescription
drugs, illegal drugs or alcohol. But just

21:01.060 --> 21:05.664 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
a fraction of those people, only 10 percent,
get meaningful help. The report cites missed

21:05.764 --> 21:10.669 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
opportunities for prevention and treatment
and it says our substance abuse costs the

21:10.769 --> 21:17.443 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
country a staggering 440 billion a year. I m
joined by the US surgeon general Dr. Vivek

21:17.543 --> 21:19.411 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Murthy. Dr. , thank you very much for being
here.

21:19.512 --> 21:21.280 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
VIVEK MURTHY, US SURGEON GENERAL: Really glad
to be with you.

21:21.380 --> 21:26.819 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
BRANGHAM: This is a pretty sobering report.
Millions of people suffering, very, very few

21:26.919 --> 21:31.290 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
people are getting help. When you compiled
all this data, were you surprised by what

21:31.390 --> 21:33.192 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you had found?

21:33.292 --> 21:40.032 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MURTHY: Well, I had seen the problem up close
as a doctor practicing medicine. When I came

21:40.132 --> 21:45.571 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
into medicine, I expected as an internal medicine
doctor to primarily see people with diabetes,

21:45.671 --> 21:51.744 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
heart disease and cancer, and I was shocked
by the number of patients who came under my

21:51.844 --> 21:53.546 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
care who actually had substance abuse.

21:53.646 --> 21:56.582 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
BRANGHAM: You were seeing this in private
practice before being tapped to be in the

21:56.682 --> 21:58.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
federal government?

21:58.484 --> 22:01.320 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MURTHY: Yes, I have always seen this -- we
even -- starting in medical school itself

22:01.420 --> 22:02.321 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and then on throughout

22:02.421 --> 22:04.190 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
[0: 25: 00. 1]

22:04.290 --> 22:07.226 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
my medical career, the experience was not
unique to me but many of my clinician colleagues

22:07.326 --> 22:09.962 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
were seeing the same thing and they were really
surprised.

22:10.062 --> 22:13.332 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
When I became surgeon general and had the
privilege of travelling around the country

22:13.432 --> 22:18.337 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
and hearing people s stories firsthand, I
found that every community was touched in

22:18.437 --> 22:24.610 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
some way by substance abuse disorders. I went
to a small fishing village in Alaska called

22:24.710 --> 22:29.882 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Napaskiak which is accessible only by boat
and no roads to go there and even in this

22:29.982 --> 22:35.521 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
small village of less than 500 people, the
small little building where they kept medications

22:35.621 --> 22:40.392 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
had been broken into multiple times by people
seeking out prescription painkillers.

22:40.492 --> 22:44.997 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
BRANGHAM: You say in this report that we as
a nation need to think differently about addiction

22:45.097 --> 22:49.468 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
and to look at substance abuse and addiction
differently. How do we look at it now and

22:49.568 --> 22:51.303 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
what would you like to see change?

22:51.403 --> 22:56.041 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MURTHY: Unfortunately, for too many people,
addiction is a disease of choice, they see

22:56.141 --> 23:01.180 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
as a character flaw as evidence of moral failing,
but what we know they are clearly from the

23:01.280 --> 23:05.217 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
science, is that addiction is actually none
of those things it s a chronic disease of

23:05.317 --> 23:07.019 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the brain.

23:07.119 --> 23:11.557 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
We have good scientific studies that tell
us that addiction impacts the circuits in

23:11.657 --> 23:16.662 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
your brain and in specific parts of the brain
that affect impulse control, decision making

23:16.762 --> 23:21.367 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
and your stress and reward response. When
we understand that, we start to have a better

23:21.467 --> 23:26.405 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
sense of why it is so easy for people to relapse
with substance abuse disorders and why people

23:26.505 --> 23:28.507 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
experience withdrawal symptoms and cravings.

23:28.607 --> 23:34.513 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
BRANGHAM: Can you explain -- that number really
jumps, 440 billion dollars in costs from substance

23:34.613 --> 23:37.416 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
abuse. How do the costs add up?

23:37.516 --> 23:42.221 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MURTHY: These costs come from several streams.
One is from direct healthcare costs. Also

23:42.321 --> 23:48.761 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
losses in workplace productivity as well as
criminal justice system costs. The good news

23:48.861 --> 23:53.732 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
is we have evidence-based treatment and prevention
strategies at work. The problem is they re

23:53.832 --> 23:55.534 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
just not getting it to enough people.

23:55.634 --> 24:00.472 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
BRANGHAM: Why is that? You report details
quite a bit of these things that you argue

24:00.572 --> 24:04.143 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
absolutely are proven to work but aren t being
used, why is that?

24:04.243 --> 24:07.680 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MURTHY: It s really striking and it s especially
striking when you recognize it. Not only do

24:07.780 --> 24:11.517 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
we have a humanitarian reason to get treatments
to people but we know that for every dollar

24:11.617 --> 24:15.020 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
that we invest in treatment we save four dollars
in healthcare costs, seven dollars in criminal

24:15.120 --> 24:20.926 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
justice system costs. We have prevention programs
that are proven, that can save up to 64 dollars

24:21.026 --> 24:22.861 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
for every one dollar invested.

24:22.961 --> 24:26.332 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
A part of the reason that people haven t gotten
these treatments is that, as a country, number

24:26.432 --> 24:31.070 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
one, we haven t invested enough in expansion
of treatment programs. Number two, we haven t

24:31.170 --> 24:35.808 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
trained our clinicians widely enough in how
to recognize, diagnose and treat substance

24:35.908 --> 24:41.580 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
abuse disorders and, third, there is this
ongoing, unfortunate stigma around substance

24:41.680 --> 24:45.651 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
abuse disorders that prevents people fromseeking help in the first place.

24:45.751 --> 24:50.856 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
BRANGHAM: On the prevention side, what is
it that works? What is it that we know can

24:50.956 --> 24:54.760 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
be done to help people to stop these substanceabuse problems from developing?

24:54.860 --> 24:59.164 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MURTHY: Well, the good news is that, there
are prevention programs that don t just target

24:59.264 --> 25:04.236 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
one particular kind of substance but they
can be effective reducing rates of use of

25:04.336 --> 25:09.475 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
alcohol, tobacco as well as elicit substances
particularly by our youth and these programs

25:09.575 --> 25:15.381 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
are varied but some of them are school-based
programs, one called the behavior game which

25:15.481 --> 25:21.253 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
trains young children in how to deal with
stress in a healthy way and how to understand

25:21.353 --> 25:26.125 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
some of these substances of misuse and understand
how to deal with them responsibly.

25:26.225 --> 25:31.497 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
There are also community-based programs that
focus on education and on dealing with stress

25:31.597 --> 25:36.001 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
in a healthy way. And this is a key point
which is, as I ve traveled around the country,

25:36.101 --> 25:41.173 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
I have found many times when people are using
substances or when they begin, they begin

25:41.273 --> 25:45.477 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
