01:03:01.911 --> 01:03:03.613 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
We didn t just look at opioids but we also
looked at alcohol, and it may surprise many

01:03:03.713 --> 01:03:04.147 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
people to recognize that alcohol leads to
the other substances in terms of cost and

01:03:04.247 --> 01:03:06.082 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
lives lost.

01:03:06.182 --> 01:03:06.883 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So we dealt with a range of substances. If
you read the report carefully where you understand

01:03:06.983 --> 01:03:07.450 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
there is in fact a road map

01:03:07.550 --> 01:03:09.252 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
[0: 30: 00. 2]

01:03:09.352 --> 01:03:11.221 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
for how we should approach prevention and
how we should approach treatment, there is

01:03:11.321 --> 01:03:13.023 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
also attention to given to recovery because
what we have realized over time is that treatment

01:03:13.123 --> 01:03:14.858 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
is not a two-week process where you go in,
get cured and are good to go. Instead, we

01:03:14.958 --> 01:03:16.793 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
have to focus on long-term treatment because
this is a chronic illness. We give a fair

01:03:16.893 --> 01:03:18.161 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
