01:08:50.560 --> 01:08:51.294 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
YANG: From food to drink, our Thanksgiving
meal theme continues with a story about a

01:08:51.394 --> 01:08:53.229 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
new vintage from South Africa.

01:08:53.329 --> 01:08:54.664 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Special correspondent Martin Seemungal brings
us the story of some fledgling vintners trying

01:08:54.764 --> 01:08:55.298 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
their hands at the ancient craft in the unlikeliest
of places.

01:08:55.398 --> 01:08:57.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

01:08:57.367 --> 01:08:59.202 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL, PBS NEWSHOUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT
(voice-over): South Africa s breathtaking

01:08:59.302 --> 01:09:01.004 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
vineyards near Cape Town, perfectly manicured
estates spreading for miles in every direction,

01:09:01.104 --> 01:09:02.839 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
famous for world class wines. But a world
away, from the sprawling townships on the

01:09:02.939 --> 01:09:04.674 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
outskirts of the city -- infamous for forced
resettlement of mixed race and black South

01:09:04.774 --> 01:09:06.542 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Africans, for crime and poverty -- you have
to look pretty hard to find a common link

01:09:06.642 --> 01:09:08.411 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
-- but it is there, one little square among
a sea of shacks: a man planting a vineyard.

01:09:08.511 --> 01:09:10.246 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Manelisi Mapukata is part of an innovative
collective; growing wine grapes in small plots

01:09:10.346 --> 01:09:12.148 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
that will one day make wine. The township
winery started production using grapes from

01:09:12.248 --> 01:09:14.050 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
those traditional winemaking areas, Sauvignon
Blanc, Chardonnay, Pinotage, but the labels

01:09:14.150 --> 01:09:15.318 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
are unique... The Flats, Philippi, names from
this part of town. Ultimately, more and more

01:09:15.418 --> 01:09:17.186 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
of the grapes will come from these tiny township
plots.

01:09:17.286 --> 01:09:19.022 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
MANELISI MAPUKATA, VINEYARD FARMER: I feel
proud about it because if just give me enough

01:09:19.122 --> 01:09:20.623 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
time also I will learn more about grapes.
How it s important to have in our townships.

01:09:20.723 --> 01:09:22.525 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
People can learn. People can come to visitalso to see what is happening.

01:09:22.625 --> 01:09:24.327 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: The vines he is planting here won t
actually be ready to bear fruit for another

01:09:24.427 --> 01:09:25.094 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
three years, but after that, he will have
a guaranteed harvest every year, and that

01:09:25.194 --> 01:09:27.096 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
means a guaranteed income.

01:09:27.196 --> 01:09:28.931 align:left position:62.5%,start line:86.67% size:37.5%
That guaranteed income is an enormously important
project to the farmers. Many have spent years

01:09:29.032 --> 01:09:30.733 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
growing and selling vegetables and have been
at the mercy of fluctuating prices. Those

01:09:30.833 --> 01:09:31.901 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
empty rows in a section of this small plot
will soon be growing grapes and ultimately

01:09:32.001 --> 01:09:32.869 align:left position:62.5%,start line:93.33% size:37.5%
earn annually as much as all vegetables combined.

01:09:32.969 --> 01:09:34.704 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
Lulama says it will change their lives.

01:09:34.804 --> 01:09:36.205 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
LULAMA, VINEYARD FARMER: It means that we
want to generate more income so that we can

01:09:36.305 --> 01:09:38.007 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
put bread on the table for our children and
the generations to come.

01:09:38.107 --> 01:09:39.876 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: They stand to double what they
are making now. The average income here is

01:09:39.976 --> 01:09:41.744 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
roughly $1,800 a year. Easy to understand
why people are energized, why word is spreading.

01:09:41.844 --> 01:09:43.279 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Nomhle Zondani is marketing the Township Winery
internationally, and here in South Africa,

01:09:43.379 --> 01:09:45.214 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
she also has to manage expectations amongthese first time growers.

01:09:45.314 --> 01:09:47.216 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
NOMHLE ZONDANI, MARKETER, THE TOWNSHIP WINERY:
Its not going to be an easy money making scheme.

01:09:47.316 --> 01:09:49.052 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
You re not going to get rich in like two years.
So, within that five years, you will get exposure.

01:09:49.152 --> 01:09:50.953 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
We will bring people to say this is an idea
that we have we would love to grow it and

01:09:51.054 --> 01:09:51.387 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
after five years, we would then we will have
this whatever grape we can harvest from those

01:09:51.487 --> 01:09:53.256 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
vines.

01:09:53.356 --> 01:09:55.058 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: Graham Knox is an expert with years
of experience at all levels of winemaking,

01:09:55.158 --> 01:09:56.159 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
now a key partner in the township winery.
Hard as it is to believe he says the soil

01:09:56.259 --> 01:09:57.994 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
in these townships is perfect for wine grapes.

01:09:58.094 --> 01:09:59.796 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
GRAHAM KNOX, THE TOWNSHIP WINERY: To grow
vines in the townships brings a response of

01:09:59.896 --> 01:10:01.664 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
surprise, incredulousness. And this is an
opportunity to take the land that s in the

01:10:01.764 --> 01:10:03.599 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
township that doesn t have that huge price
tag to enable the ladies to benefit from their

01:10:03.699 --> 01:10:04.167 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
works to make a living from growing vines
and grapes in a way that is completely impossible

01:10:04.267 --> 01:10:06.069 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Stellenbosch.

01:10:06.169 --> 01:10:08.004 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: Stellenbosch -- about an hour away
-- is home to some of South Africa s premier

01:10:08.104 --> 01:10:09.605 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
wine estates. Warwick is one of them, a pioneer
in its own right. Nearly 40 years ago, Warwick s

01:10:09.705 --> 01:10:11.507 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Norma Ratcliffe was one of the first womento make wine in South Africa.

01:10:11.607 --> 01:10:13.376 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
NORMA RATCLIFFE, WARWICK WINE ESTATE: I started
with six barrels of wine, and I went through

01:10:13.476 --> 01:10:15.178 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
all the stages that they will go through,
and a part of being a woman winemaker in those

01:10:15.278 --> 01:10:17.013 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
days was novelty. Part of their project is
novelty which will take them quite far as

01:10:17.113 --> 01:10:18.915 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
well. People come they want to have a look.
Hey, these guys are doing something neat.

01:10:19.015 --> 01:10:20.817 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: The plan is to showcase that novelty
by converting this old cement factory in one

01:10:20.917 --> 01:10:21.784 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
of the townships to a winery Knox hopes that
in a few years time, it will be ready to process

01:10:21.884 --> 01:10:22.885 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
the grapes that will be harvested here.

01:10:22.985 --> 01:10:24.554 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
KNOX: And start to come in to those big windows.

01:10:24.654 --> 01:10:26.389 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: He says it will be the focal pointof the township winery project.

01:10:26.489 --> 01:10:28.157 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
KNOX: People who drink wine absolutely love
to visit wineries. International press and

01:10:28.257 --> 01:10:29.959 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
wine traders are fascinated by the idea that
we want to grow grapes in the township.

01:10:30.059 --> 01:10:31.761 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: And there is more to this story
than the novelty of growing grapes in the

01:10:31.861 --> 01:10:33.663 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
township and the economic benefits it will
provide. For decades black and mixed race

01:10:33.763 --> 01:10:34.464 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
south Africans were the laborers in the wine
estates. With only a few exceptions, ownership

01:10:34.564 --> 01:10:36.332 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
has remained in white hands.

01:10:36.432 --> 01:10:38.201 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Arlene Van Wyk says her father and grandfather
were wine farm workers. She says the idea

01:10:38.301 --> 01:10:38.968 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
of being a winegrower was always an impossible
dream. But now, she s preparing the ground

01:10:39.068 --> 01:10:40.770 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
to plant her own vineyard.

01:10:40.870 --> 01:10:42.472 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
ARLENE VAN WYK, VINEYARD FARMER: I ve been
waiting all my life. I ve been poor all my

01:10:42.572 --> 01:10:44.373 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
life. So, now, today, even the farm workers
kids can even now become farmers.

01:10:44.474 --> 01:10:46.209 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
For me, there s a big change in the last 30
years. There s a lot of white people out there

01:10:46.309 --> 01:10:48.144 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
that wants to help us as colored people and
black people. The more doors it will open,

01:10:48.244 --> 01:10:49.045 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
more of our black people will have opportunity
to have our own vineyards, our own wine cellars

01:10:49.145 --> 01:10:50.847 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
and obviously sell the best wines.

01:10:50.947 --> 01:10:51.481 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: Norma Ratcliffe understands the
impact apartheid had and believes this is

01:10:51.581 --> 01:10:53.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
an important step.

01:10:53.416 --> 01:10:55.218 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
RATCLIFFE: I think its going to give these
people a lot more than a stake. I think its

01:10:55.318 --> 01:10:55.718 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
going to give them a bit of upliftment. It s
going to say I m doing something and I m worth

01:10:55.818 --> 01:10:57.553 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
something.

01:10:57.653 --> 01:10:59.222 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: Lulama has turned a dusty corner
of Guletu Township into an oasis of hope,

01:10:59.322 --> 01:11:01.090 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
and she is deeply proud, even though it is
in the middle of a poor township.

01:11:01.190 --> 01:11:02.592 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
LULAMA: I don t think the beauty of the place
matters. What matters is that you do what

01:11:02.692 --> 01:11:04.427 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
you want to do. You want to succeed. You want
to reach your goals.

01:11:04.527 --> 01:11:06.262 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
SEEMUNGAL: They understand success will not
come easy. But these new winegrowers -- in

01:11:06.362 --> 01:11:07.630 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
the most unlikely of places are determined
to get there -- one tiny vineyard at a time.

01:11:07.730 --> 01:11:08.197 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
For the "PBS NewsHour", I m Martin Seemungal
in Cape Town.

01:11:08.297 --> 01:11:10.099 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEOTAPE)

01:11:10.199 --> 01:11:11.968 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
YANG: Finally tonight, another in our "Brief
But Spectacular" series where we ask. Tonight,

01:11:12.068 --> 01:11:13.302 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
we hear from Steve Cohen, owner of New York s
Second Avenue Deli, who gives us his take

01:11:13.402 --> 01:11:13.936 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
on the pastrami, sliced thin with the side
of schmoozing.

01:11:14.036 --> 01:11:15.771 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

01:11:15.872 --> 01:11:17.640 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
STEVE COHEN, NEW YORK S SECOND AVENUE DELI:
You meet people in the deli, and it s like

01:11:17.740 --> 01:11:19.542 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
you re their best friend. I saw it here in
1981, right before Passover. My favorite part

01:11:19.642 --> 01:11:21.410 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
of the job is meeting people, talking to people.
I have people that came in as customers and

01:11:21.511 --> 01:11:22.078 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
now they are friends. I go to their weddings,
their bar mitzvahs, and, unfortunately, I

01:11:22.178 --> 01:11:24.046 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
go to their deaths.

01:11:24.147 --> 01:11:25.915 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
You know, it s a good business from a social
standpoint. As a business, it s a little difficult

01:11:26.015 --> 01:11:26.549 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
kosher deli business. The food cost is quite
large. Nobody has to throw a benefit for us,

01:11:26.649 --> 01:11:28.451 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
but it is a fact.

01:11:28.551 --> 01:11:29.552 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
We have vats and vats of beats. It s briskets.
We have roast beefs. We have pastramis. They

01:11:29.652 --> 01:11:31.420 align:left position:75%,start line:93.33% size:25%
have to be steamed properly. They kept properly.

01:11:31.521 --> 01:11:33.256 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
So, it s just a little more difficult to run
and to make money at, to tell you the truth.

01:11:33.356 --> 01:11:34.790 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
There is a lot of exclusive restaurants in
New York that shall remain nameless. You go

01:11:34.891 --> 01:11:36.592 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
to those restaurants and say, look what Ihave, look what I can do.

01:11:36.692 --> 01:11:38.227 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
They come to a deli and you say, you know
what? Look what we have. Look what we can

01:11:38.327 --> 01:11:40.129 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
do. We re all a group and friends. And theytalk. It s the great equalizer.

01:11:40.229 --> 01:11:41.097 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
When you come to New York, one of the reasons
is pastrami or deli. We have the matzo ball

01:11:41.197 --> 01:11:42.999 align:left position:87.5%,start line:93.33% size:12.5%
soup. We have a fresh stock pot going.

01:11:43.099 --> 01:11:44.834 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
Our pastrami is mouth watering. You just slice
thin. It s the bacaya (ph), which is a gift.

01:11:44.934 --> 01:11:46.369 align:left position:75%,start line:86.67% size:25%
